    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <head>55. Memorandum From the Administrator of the Agency for International
                    Development (<persName corresp="#p_GWS1" type="from">Gaud</persName>) to
                    President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d55fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Subject File, Foreign Aid [1 of 3], Box 16. Limited Official
                        Use. A handwritten note on the source text by <persName corresp="#p_REVD1"
                            >Rostow</persName> reads: “OK W”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-10-06">October 6, 1966</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1967 Foreign Assistance Appropriations
                            Act<note n="2" xml:id="d55fn2">P.L. 89–691 was approved on October 5,
                            1966. (80 Stat. 1018)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The Conference on the Foreign Assistance Appropriations Act for <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1967 met this afternoon and completed its work in
                    45 minutes.</p>
                <p>The amounts appropriated for Foreign Assistance Act activities, compared with the
                    budgets requests, are: <pb facs="0194" n="160" xml:id="pg_160"/>
                    <table cols="3" rows="5">
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Budget Request</hi>
                            </cell>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Appropriation</hi>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell cols="2">(<hi rend="italic">in millions of dollars</hi>)</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Economic</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$2,469</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$2144</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Military</cell>
                            <cell role="num">917</cell>
                            <cell role="num">792</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>TOTAL</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$3,386</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$2,936</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>The $2,936 million, which is the same total as the Senate bill, is the lowest
                    appropriation for foreign assistance since <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                    1958. It is clear from our talks with Senator Pastore that if the House
                    conferees had tried harder (the House bill was $110 million higher than the
                    Senate bill), we could have done better.<note n="3" xml:id="d55fn3">At the end
                        of this paragraph a handwritten notation by President <persName
                            corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> reads: “Why didn’t you and your
                        people live with these conferees? L”</note>
                </p>
                <p>We are particularly squeezed in four appropriation categories: <table cols="3"
                        rows="6">
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Budget Request</hi>
                            </cell>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Appropriation</hi>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell cols="2">(<hi rend="italic">in millions of dollars</hi>)</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Development Loans</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$665</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$500</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Supporting Assistance (including Vietnam)</cell>
                            <cell role="num">747</cell>
                            <cell role="num">690</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Contingency Fund</cell>
                            <cell role="num">70</cell>
                            <cell role="num">35</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Military Assistance</cell>
                            <cell role="num">917</cell>
                            <cell role="num">792</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>One other item of significance. The conferees agreed (a) to amend Section 205 of
                    the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 so that it will permit—rather than
                    require—the transfer of 10% of Development Loan funds to the World Bank
                        family<note n="4" xml:id="d55fn4">Section 205 of the Foreign Assistance Act
                        of 1961, as amended in P.L. 89–579, approved on September 16, 1966. (80
                        Stat. 797)</note> and (b) to drop the annual prohibition in the
                    Appropriations Act on the use of load funds for transfer to the World Bank
                    family.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">
                            <hi rend="strong">William S. Gaud</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
